Text.SourceString: You’re the new arrival, huh?//Don’t bother me, and I won’t bother you.//<portrait=determined>Hah! <Italic>Syke</>!
You’re in my way.//No, seriously, you <Italic>are</> in my way.
Got business with me?
I can't chit-chat all day.//Talk to someone else, will you?
The beach shack has people in it if you want to chat.
There are plenty of rooms over there if you wanna sit down.
You can't dive from here...you gotta go there.//Go to the inn, then go south. You can dive from there.
My job’s not just a day at the beach. I have to be on the lookout all the time.//It only takes a split second for somebody to get into trouble in the water.
And those riptides are no joke!//People think they’re good swimmers, but the waves will pull you under in a split second.
Didn’t mean to freak you out! It’s calm most of the time. But when a lifeguard tells you to stay near the shore, pay attention.//<portrait=determined>We’re just looking out for you.
I started lifeguarding in high school and just stuck with it, I guess.//It’s not a hard job, and it helps me stay in shape.
Volleyball – that’s my real passion. Do you play?
Join me some time. We’ll get a game going. Gotta warn you, though. I play to win.

It’s cool if it’s not your thing. I won’t hold it against you.//<portrait=determined>I mean, to me, a life without volleyball seems like a pretty sad existence, but I guess you feel the same way about a life without…I dunno…corn?//<portrait=normal>Whatever you grow at your farm.
I’m <Italic>starving</>.//Training always makes you hungry.
Gimme some carbs, you know what I mean? Pizza, pasta, gnocchi…ramen!//<portrait=happy>I would kill for some ramen right now.
How about this weather, huh? Rainy one day, sunny the next. Bah!
I had no idea what to expect when I woke up this morning.
How about this weather, huh? Rainy one day, sunny the next. Bah!
I had no idea what to expect when I woke up this morning.
The hot spring is really good for sore muscles. Nothing beats a hot soak after a hard workout.
Yikes, this rain! I’ve never seen anything like it!
Yikes, this rain! I’ve never seen anything like it!
Yikes, this rain! I’ve never seen anything like it!
Ey, check out my new sneakers! They give me extra spring in my toes. Perfect for volleyball.
I paid way too much for these shoes. Hopefully they’re going to up my game.
There’s this pink tree next to the hot spring.//Do you know what it is? Cherry, maybe?
It’s pretty, but I’m worried the petals will clog up the drain…<Italic>my</> drain.
Watch out for jellyfish on the beach.//Don't get stung by one.
Oof, the beach is gross today. Smells like dead fish.
I think it’s just some seaweed that washed up, but still. Ugh.
This storm is wild! The beach is going to be a mess tomorrow.//All sorts of trash and debris washes up after weather like this.
It’s almost the end of the year already… Fast, huh?
I might take a class online, learning new things.//Not right now. I’m way too busy. But maybe this Winter, when it’s too cold for volleyball.
Winter’s almost here.
I still run to the beach from my house, but the snow slows me down! Bah!//And when it’s icy, forget it. Trying to run on ice is a sure way to break a bone.
The hot spring sounds good right now.//<portrait=annoyed>What is it?
I’m so itchy today! I’ve got bug bites all over my legs.//Full forced bugs. Great!
The weather is warming up.//Anything more than what I'm wearing will make me sweat <Italic>buckets</>.
It’s Spring, baby! Time to hit the volleyball court and work off my Winter blues!
I managed to stay in pretty good shape over the Winter, but I feel a little off my game, you know?//<portrait=determined>I’m itching to get a good workout in.
You know that plastic rings six packs come in?//<portrait=sad>They can kill sea life if they end up in the ocean. It’s so sad.
Don't forget to dispose of the six-pack rings properly after picnics. You hear?
I don't like staying indoors too long...sitting behind a desk. Bah!
The human body was built to move.
There's usually an influx of people visiting the beach in Summer.//I get it. Summer...beach. Yeah, whatever.
I start seeing more and more people busting out their bathing suits.
Never buying from White Flamingo again.//Got a new trunk and...
I hadn't even worn it once!//The first wash and it shrunk. Dang it!
Stargazing is cool.//Didn't think so at first, but now I’m living at the observatory, I kinda get it.
You either get it or you don't with this thing.//If you don't get it, then your lost.
If <NPCName>Zoe</>’s serious about volleyball, I will take her under my wing.
I was about her age when I started playing. It’s never too early.
I was gonna get in some volleyball time, but it’s just too wet out there. Bah!
Guess I’ll have to stay inside today.
I was gonna get in some volleyball time, but it’s just too wet out there. Bah!
Guess I’ll have to stay inside today.
Did you see a pair of sunglasses here somewhere?//I lost them. I’m sure I had them yesterday at work…
Oh <Italic>man</>! I forgot that I let <NpcName>Wakuu</> borrow them.
<NpcName>Zarah</> was using a metal detector down on the beach the other day, and she found a gold coin.
You think there might be more?!//I should invest in a metal detector…
Found a pearl at the beach the other day...not yours, is it?
Sports teach humility... I like that.//Sometimes we win and sometimes we lose.
So what if you lose? Gotta brace it and try again tomorrow.//It's not the end of the world.
I used to swim a lot when I was a kid, but it didn't grip me...not competitive enough, I think.
I like playing sports where there are winners and losers.
I jacked up my knee yesterday. Falling off the stairs in front of the bathhouse, tripped on some leaves. Bah!
It hurts a bit when I walk... I guess this is a glimpse into what old age will feel like.
Apple is in season, no? Do you have them in your farm, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
What's with the giant chicken they put in Harvest Festival, huh? So weird!
Where do you think I can get one of those?
I cleaned the leaves in front of the bath house yesterday and it's already piling up again.
Need to find <NpcName>Wakuu</>. It's his turn to clear the path for <NpcName>Takeba</>.
It’s freezing today. Do a few jumping jacks or push-ups if you wanna get toasty warm.//Try it.
Is getting hand mittens worth it, you reckon? You look like the type to have a lot of those things.
I'll see if <NpcName>Wakuu</> has some and test drive them, maybe.
Dry air...bah!//What is it?
One of those giant animal suits from White Flamingo would be nice.//<portrait=determined>Nice and toasty inside.
<NpcName>Wakuu</> goes to see his dad every weekend like a clockwork.//Comes Satuday, place is all mine until Monday.

I know that <NpcName>Wataru</> gardens at his house. Has a small patch in front of the lighthouse...//<NpcName>Wakuu</> always brings some random crops back to the observatory. Taste great! Really fresh.//<portrait=concerned>What do they do now that Winter is here? Can't be gardening, can it?
Are you doing one of those year's resolution <Italic>thing</>?//<portrait=determined>Mine is the same every year: get better at life.
I started lifeguarding during my last Summer of high school. This was before I moved to Coral Island.//<portrait=happy>I didn’t think I’d still be doing it all these years later, but no complaints.
I only work the afternoon shift, giving me lots of volleyball practice time.//<portrait=determined>Gotta keep my eyes on the prize, you know what I mean?
I’ve been swimming for years, but you know what I wish I did more of? Diving.
Maybe I could train to be a deep sea diver. Who knows?
You know the Hillside observatory? I live out there.
Kind of a hike to get to the beach, but I like that about it. Keeps me in shape, you know?
Up for some game?
Might stop by the Beach Shack later...pick up some coconuts.//I'm kinda in the mood for it.
I like playing volleyball with <NPCName>Aaliyah</>.//We both play hard, you know what I mean?
Have you seen that dog running around town? Taco?//<portrait=happy>I love that scruffy guy.
This one time I saw Taco swimming in the fountain... Yeah, the one in front of the general store.//<portrait=happy>What a funny little dude.

I’ve thought about getting a pet, but between volleyball practice and workouts and work, I’m hardly ever home to take care of one.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t want to be cooped up in my house like <NpcName>Wakuu</>, and that’s not fair to a pet.
Unless I brought them out with me. I hadn’t thought about that.
Who made the sign for Beach Shack?//<portrait=annoyed>The coconut drink signs say buy two get two. Reminds me of what my dad would make.
Are you here to eat, <PlayerName>$player</>?
<NPCName>Frank</>’s pesto pasta is good.//<portrait=happy>Easy to overeat.
I hate to think about getting older.//<portrait=determined>I’m in the prime of my life, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m in the best shape now that I’ve ever been.
But it doesn’t last forever, you know?//You don’t see grandparents competing in the Pokyo Volleyball Tournament.
I feel dizzy... My head...//Whoaaa... I might've caught something.
Hmm... Should I get my flu shot now? Kinda don't wanna go to the clinic.//Not a fan of going to clinics or hospitals... That's where <Italic>sick</> people go, you know what I mean?
I'm sure the one in town is cleaner than my room, but who knows what kind of germs or viruses are there?*shivers*
I'm not in the mood.
